               </MAIN_SITE>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>A formal procurement exercise to appoint a contractor will be undertaken, but the Council is keen to give potential contractors an overview of the outline scope of work required, invite comments and provide clarity on the requirements.</P>
                  <P>Potential bidders are invited to attend a Q&amp;A meeting with the Council team, at a mutually convenient time, and can visit the site if required. The meeting should last no more than an hour. Alternatively, a telephone call can be arranged.</P>
                  <P>Contractors who would like to request to take part in a meeting or telephone Q&amp;A session with the Council are requested to submit their request by email to Carol Morgan to the following email address Carol.morgan@swansea.gov.uk</P>
                  <P>Q&amp;A sessions will be purely informal and will not form part of any subsequent procurement process.</P>
                  <P>Swansea Council wishes to appoint a multi-disciplinary team for architecture and design services to assist the Council in developing a masterplan for a large council housing site in the city.</P>
                  <P>Whilst refurbishment of properties to Welsh Housing Quality Standard (WHQS) has been recommended for other sites, various issues mainly due to design, layout and long term sustainability, mean that a different approach may be required.</P>
                  <P>The team will work with the Council to assess options for redevelopment, or a combination of redevelopment and refurbishment, with the opportunity to redesign the layout, density, including a mixed tenure approach, and increase the number of homes on the site by utilising vacant land within the site.</P>
                  <P>Not responding to this Prior Information Notice shall not prevent any contractor from participating in any future procurement process.</P>
                  <P>The publication of this Prior Information Notice does not signify the beginning of any formal procurement process and does not constitute a commitment by the Council to undertake any future procurement process.</P>
                  <P>The Council may withdraw or amend any information contained in this Prior Information Notice at any time and without notice.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
